                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15497098" author="jwagenleitner" created="Fri, 16 Sep 2016 18:55:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like the case for &lt;tt&gt;def m = foo 1&lt;/tt&gt; was fixed in 1.8.  So probably would be good to remove the last line in the example and the &lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;...or on the right-hand side of an assignment&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt; wording.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15500761" author="paulk" created="Sun, 18 Sep 2016 10:42:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15512228" author="jwagenleitner" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 05:31:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting!  Removed the incorrect example and wording and added a note about methods with no args instead to match up with the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.groovy-lang.org/semantics.html#_optional_parentheses&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Optional Parentheses&lt;/em&gt; section of the semantics guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/a982938330094fab0548ea6e31278a8821a5536d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/a982938330094fab0548ea6e31278a8821a5536d&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15521448" author="tinne" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2016 21:29:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the rapid documentation update. I am however afraid that &quot;&lt;tt&gt;def m = bar&lt;/tt&gt; won&apos;t work&quot; may be a bit brief explanation, as indeed, the assignment does work, but not as one might possibly expect: it defines &lt;tt&gt;m&lt;/tt&gt; as an alternative variable to denote the closure the name &lt;tt&gt;bar&lt;/tt&gt; is currenly assigned to.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not explained in either the style guide or the semantics document.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15522054" author="jwagenleitner" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2016 04:59:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The following from the change throws a &lt;tt&gt;groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException: No such property: bar for class: Test&lt;/tt&gt; on 2.4.7 which is the same sort of error the single param foo method gives when in a nested call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Test.groovy&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def bar() { 1 }
def m = bar
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It sounds like you might be referring to the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.groovy-lang.org/latest/html/documentation/#method-pointer-operator&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Method Pointer Operator (.&amp;amp;)&lt;/a&gt; and that does work:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Test.groovy&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def bar() { 1 }
def m = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;amp;bar
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; m() == 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But that is not what the example shows.  Would be happy to expand the wording of that section if you have suggested wording or a PR would be welcomed as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15543290" author="tinne" created="Mon, 3 Oct 2016 20:12:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like I stumbled over the fact that &lt;tt&gt;groovysh&lt;/tt&gt; is even less groovyish than I expected, as I falsely derived by assumptions from whatever happens here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;groovy:000&amp;gt; bar = { -&amp;gt; 1 }
===&amp;gt; groovysh_evaluate$_run_closure1@5812f68b
groovy:000&amp;gt; m = bar
===&amp;gt; groovysh_evaluate$_run_closure1@5812f68b
groovy:000&amp;gt; m()
===&amp;gt; 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems to be yet something different, as the following assignment gives a different closure behaving the same way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;groovy:000&amp;gt; m = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;amp;bar
===&amp;gt; org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.MethodClosure@5e4bd84a
groovy:000&amp;gt; m()
===&amp;gt; 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15543964" author="paulk" created="Tue, 4 Oct 2016 01:05:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, are you saying you are happy to mark as &quot;Resolved&quot; or further clarification required?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15546542" author="tinne" created="Tue, 4 Oct 2016 20:18:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is certainly resolved, thanks for nudging.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
